description: While everyone anxiously awaits the verdict on the "Day 204" trial, Matty takes to the streets and visits the site of the massacre, the memorial, and talks to residents who got caught in the crossfire.
name: Friendly Fire, 3 of 5

description: Matty is called in for an exclusive, on-the-record interview with a top-level commander who was in charge the day of the brutal "Day 204" massacre. But given what Matty already knows about the day's events, he's less than impressed with the commander's version.
name: Friendly Fire, 4 of 5

description: Continuing his investigation into the "hidden war" of the thousands of people stuck in the DMZ, Matty Roth turns his attention to Amina, last seen blaming Matty for ruining her life at the end of "Public Works." True to her word, Amina now lives worse than a homeless person, which takes on a whole new meaning in a warzone.
name: Amina

description: One wild night in the life of the DMZ! We follow DJ Random Fire as he spends a rough day - dodging bullets, ex-girlfriends, and rivals in the club scene - in preparation for a show that night.
name: Random Fire

description: As yet another round of reconciliation talks begin between the U.S. government and the Free States, a new player emerges, combining political charisma and military cunning. Could the DMZ's answer to Che Guevara be the key to healing the DMZ, or does he have other intentions?
name: Blood in the Game, 1 of 6

description: After years in the DMZ, Matty Roth has been faced with numerous challenges, but for the first time ever, he's faced with rejection, as his story on a revolutionary named Delgado is rejected by all news agencies. Rejection he can handle, but it's a surprise phone call that just might send Matty over the edge.
name: Blood in the Game, 2 of 6

description: As the pro-Delgado movement expands, the P.R. firms of both the United States and of the FSA attempt to get the revolutionary on their sides. But Delgado has plans of his own.
name: Blood in the Game, 3 of 6

description: Following his appearances in Cyclone Anthology In Dark Nebula's first issue there is a lot of press for a new masked hero called "Vigilante". The general at USO has asked Mark why he can't get that sort of press. Watching the news as this V gets interviewed Mark is not impressed, believing him to be a blow hard. When Mark seeks to help out when a major accident occurs on a Bridge (telekinetically holding the bridge together while emergancy services get people off), Vigilante appears and seems to get most of the credit for doing nothing. Mark is even less impressed. Finally V attacks DN and reveals that his is truly the Grandstander (the international assassin) with a contract for some of the high ranking officials at USO, since it was obvious that DN strongly involved himself in USO business he created the V to gain his measure. Grandstander fires a plasma blast at DN (believing him destroyed ) and continues to fullfil his contract. He is successful as DN arrives to late to stop him. GS is amazed that DN survived his plasma blast. When told by DN that's it's pretty hard to kill someone who's already died GS replies good to know for the future. At this point GS decides it is pointless to continue the fight (DN is p@$$ off and obviously too powerful) he fires at a support beam to put the others at risk and whil DN saves them makes his escape.Â
name: Dark Nebula

description: Riley a normal random guy who is a photographer with no real success manages to do what very little has been able to do, finding out that Batman and Bruce Wayne are the same person! As he saw this opportunity as a way to make himself rich he contacted Bruce Wayne who refused to let himself be blackmailed by this person. With a shocking conclusion involving Alfred, the threat of Riley is put to an end.
name: The Life of Riley

description: Alfred begins to remember and this all seems to be part of Hush's plans.Â  As flashbacks to the past begin to piece together Hush's plans to hurt Bruce Wayne, the question remains, is Hush really Tommy Elliot, or is he just another part in the elaborate scheme against the world's greatest detective?
name: The Shape of Things to Come, Part One

description: With her boyfriend missing and best friend murdered, Calie is beginning to realize that she may not have returned from Wonderland alone! Who is the mysterious being stalking her every step and what answers does he hold of her destiny in the battle between this world and Wonderland? The answers he holds will change everything you thought you knew about Wonderland, and pull Calie back into the world she prayed she would never see again!

Overview

Friends on a rescue mission discover that the road ahead physically changes every time they stop, speeding their descent to a dark, Orwellian world ruled by savage monstrosities. Conned into stealing the Unholy Grail, the source of unlimited power, they discover that all escapes are paved in blood.

Overview

Horrific monstrosities, roads paved with living flesh, slashing packs of snarling children and random death from every direction lace the second chapter of IDWâs thriller-chiller terror ride. In their desperate struggle to escape Foreman and his army of merciless butchers, Frank and his friends are forced ever deeper into a chaotic landscape of torment.

Overview

The third issue gets your blood pumping in its terrifying, macabre and action packed climax! After surviving his personal purgatory, Frank and the last members of his crew race against all obstacles to escape Foreman's full court attack. Finally reaching the end of the deadly road, Frank unwittingly infects our reality with a heavy dose of hell.

volume.name: Rogue Angel: Teller of Tall Tales

description: The hit movie Saw shocked the world with its twisted tale of the demented killer named Jigsaw. This unique predator always gave his victims a chance at life, if only they could figure out how to escape the demented traps Jigsaw had set for them. This comic, set in the world of Saw and released in anticipation of the upcoming Saw 2 movie, goes back in time to explore the events that spurred the transformation of mild-mannered John into monstrous Jigsaw.

In this tender, touching penultimate issue, Tony Montana discovers the joys of gardening, being a scout leader, and reading books quietly in the park meadow nearby his favorite church. Who are we freaking kidding? A lot of people want Tony Montana dead, and Tony's gonna cuss up a storm, snort up a small mountain of drugs, and shoot in the face anybody who ticks him off! Featuring art and a cover by Dave Crosland, as well as an incentive cover by artist Mike Huddleston.
name: Mutually Assured Destruction

description: It's the end of the line for Tony Montana, who's currently stuck in a South American prison being tortured by his most hated enemy. There's no way he's gonna get out of this, is there? Of course, on the off-chance Tony does escape, there is going to be an almost unimaginable amount of hell to pay, as Tony exacts a furious vengeance, in bodies, bullets and blood.
name: Top O' The Heap, End O' The Line

description: Say hello to IDW's gun-toting, profanity-spewing, law-breaking, drug-peddling leeeetle friend. Tony Montana, is back, you stinking cock-a-roaches, in the savage sequel to the legendary '80s-era Miami gangster movie, Scarface. Our blood-soaked tale picks up where the movie left off, as Tony survivesâjust barelyâand has to claw and kill his way back to the top of the sun-drenched Florida underworld. It ain't gonna be pretty... and a whole lot of $#@&% #%$*ers are gonna die!
name: City Of Zeroes

description: Overview In issue one, Shaun has no time for zombies; he's too busy trying to sort out his own troubled love life. Of course, zombies have a way of intruding on even the most mundane of lives.
name: Part One

description: OverviewIDW's official adaptation of last year's cult classic zombie comedy continues here. This time out, Shaun and Ed are forced to acknowledge that something isn't right in their little corner of London. Now, the easy thing would be to just stay on the couch and wait for it to pass, but then again, Shaun's girlfriend and his Mum could use his help. What's a slacker to do?
name: Part Two

description: OverviewAs Shaun and his merry band of survivors, and Ed, make they way toward the sanctuary that is the Winchester Pub, they're beset on all sides, from dissention within the ranks to indecision to zombies that are just looking for a little someone to eat. Continuing IDW's special adaptation of the zom-rom-com that the Los Angeles Times called "a grisly but sweet ode to friendship, love and the George Romero zombie trilogy."
name: Part Three

description: Our intrepid foursome has made it to the safe haven that is the Winchester Pub. At least, they thought the pub would be the best place to hide out and enjoy some pints and hog lumps while the zombie problem passed... but it seems that the zombies have other plans for Shaun, Ed, and their pals. Will Shaun have 'red' of another kind on him before all is said and done in this, the concluding chapter of IDW's special adaptation of the fan-favorite film?
name: Part Four

description: The hit Emmy- and Golden Globe-Award-winning FX TV series, The Shield, comes to comics in all its edgy, fast-paced glory! A drug bust gone sour, a stalled murder investigation, and a major traffic incident spell trouble for the cops of the Farmington District... and that's just the beginning of a bad week at the Barn!

While Claudette and Dutch try to determine the identity of an oddly familiar murder victim, the rest of the Farmington cops are caught up in a strange hostage incident, and Shane gets a job offer! The hit Fox TV series makes the transition to comics, and police work may never be the same!

With a famous victim killed on their turf, the media spotlight sits squarely on the Barn. Captain Aceveda wants everything by-the-book while the scrutiny is on, but that might cramp the Strike Team's style. And Danny and Julien differ over how to deal with a runaway... a disagreement that may have serious consequences!

name: DN2

description: DN face Chaos a force of destruction who seperates him into Mark and cerelus and sends each to different time periods to keep them in a weakened condition. Mark is sent back in time to Salem at the time of the witch hunts. Here he meets one of hisÂ ancestors and discovers that they were witches of great power as hisÂ ancestor attempts to use his power to protect innocents that are incorrectly charged. Meanwhile Cerelus is sent to the far future where Marks decendant who is the planetary protector and knows Cerelus only as a threat that was due to come from the past to destroy her time.
name: Chaos War

description: Mark and Cerelus defeat their adversaries and make their way back to their own time. Realising neither can defeat chaos alone the call a detante untill their battle with chas is over. With no ongoing fight for control chaos has no chance against DN as he is far too powreful.
name: If this is Chaos

description: While seeking out their lost war lord Cerelus the Caileijians track his thoughts to Earth and to Mark. At first they believe Mark to be Cerelus until DN attacks them believing them a threat. Being outnumbered and with Cerelus fighting him from inside DN is defeated and taken back to Caileij in the hopes of seperating Mark and Cerelus.
name: They come from Caileij

description: Mark and Cerelus are temporarily seperated and Mark is put on trial by the Caileijians for aledjed persecution of Cerelus. Mark lashes out with the dark fire and destroys all life on the planet. As Mark begins to despair what he has done his mind is touche d by Cerelus who informs that his peaple aren't dead but have evolved to the next step of evolution thanks to Marks Dark fire. Cerelus agrees as an act of gratitude to rejoin Mark as Dark Nebula. This begins a new era for Dark Nebula with all the power unfettered by the need to keep some will back to fight for control.
name: Trial of the Dark Nebula

description: The Souther Squadron is sent to bring in Dark Nebula as he has proven to be too powerful to be allowed to act unchecked,and has been blamed for many attacks on military transports. After aÂ  brief battle the Squad determines that DN is still on the side of the angels and that if he weren't theyed need a lot Â more back -up to bring him down. Due to the fact that another attack occurs while DN is with the Southern Squad (having agreed to come and clear things up) the Squad realise that the attacks were a frame up. The attacks had been occuring while DN was off planet facing judgement on Callaij. It is discovered that his enemy the grandstander used his abscence to frame him so that on his return he wouldn''t be able to trouble him as much
name: Agains the South Squad

description: Guest staring the Souther Squadron the Grandstander rears his ugly head again. The Southern Squadron join Dark Nebula in the hunt for Grandstander.Having discovered that it was actually him and not DN who had been attacking military transports. DN has a particular mad on over his name being sullied , it takes everything the SSq has to stop DN from tearing Grandstander apart.
name: Aust' greatest heroes

description: Reprinting DN's origin story originally printed in Cyclon anthalogy.
name: Origins
The Sorcerer's Apprentice; Fly Me To The Moon
Hail and Farewell!; A Whale of A Tale; The Tidy Tailor

description:
Overview
In a world of dirty politics, backstabbing friends and unfaithful women, Bill Timmons discovers that being a Snake is more than a metaphorâ¦ but heâs unprepared for what will happen when he sheds his skin and the fangs start to showâ¦ and so is everyone else.Â
name: The Subtlest Creature

description:
Overview

Love stinks. Especially when your lover has fangs. But in a Kafkaesque world of duplicitous partners and political conspiracies, sometimes the only one you can trust is the person who openly sheds his skinâ¦Â
name: Sins Of The Fathers

description: Continuing the story of past Racers throughout history! Part Han Solo, part Jack Sparrow, and all Racer, Reed Saber is a pirate king whose open road is the open seasâuntil he crosses swords with the enigmatic Ghost of the Deep, whoâs got a secret of his own! And why do both adversaries carry different halves of the same amulet? A rip-roaring adventure of swashbuckling proportions, courtesy of Arie Kaplan and Robby Musso!

volume.name: Speed Racer: Chronicles of the Racer

description: On Viden 9, the U.S.S. Enterprise encounters a planet similar to 21st century Earth, where the population has a never-ending appetite for entertainment, and people will do anything for fame. When Captain Kirk and his crew become media sensations, the competing networks that control Viden's government won't let them leave, unless Kirk agrees to a deadly "finale."

name: Cyberwar, Part 3: Along Came A Virtual Spider

description: Overview TheÂ U.S.S. EnterpriseÂ is dispatched to observe a Quark Gluon Plasma experiment at the Gemini Science Stationâin orbit between two sunsâin an effort to learn more about the beginning of the universe. But the formation of a black hole from the experiment's outcome means eminent danger for Spock and Dr. McCoy who are stranded on the debilitated science station.
Newsstand Variant cover (different coloring)
name: Virtual Mortality, Part 4: Between a Rock and a Hard Drive

description:
Overview

In this final chapter, Dynomite finally faces off with his archenemy Kane-man to man! It's an all out Kung Fu battle to the death. Can our yellow belt hero defeat his rival? Or will Kane's assortment of deadly hand weaponry prove to be the end of the super cool cat we know as Super Bad James Dynomite.
name: The Showdown

description:
Overview

Available at lastâthe long-lost episode, âThe Fall and Rise of Kingfish,â with bonus material and special features! Return to every heroâs favorite watering hole,Â The Hideout Bar & Grill, and join Guardian, Night Ranger, Scout, Rusty the Bartender and the rest of the regulars as they defend First City from the marauding Shadow-Soldiers from Dimension Z. Happy hour turns sour as one of their own loses their life in the line of duty and the group has to come to terms with the loss of a colleague. This re-mastered âlost episodeâ includes never-before-seen specially enhanced scenes, interviews with the cast, outtake and blooper scenes, and additional bonus material.
name: The Lost Episode
Cyberwar, Part 4: Spider In The Machine

description: OverviewThis time out, Cal and his ghoulish partner Mo'Lock face a prison break that signals the return of Dr. Polynice, last seen in IDW's Savage Membrane prose novel. Plus, Cal gets himself a new ride... or does the new ride get him?

volume.name: Supernatural Freak Machine: A Cal McDonald Mystery

description:
Overview

Cal's latest adventure finds his old nemesis, the modern-day Dr. Frankenstein, Dr. Polynice, releasing new horrors on the world. But before Cal can deal with him, he and Mo'Lock must contend with... a killer car?

volume.name: Supernatural Freak Machine: A Cal McDonald Mystery

name: The Lost Palace of Kashi; Snipe Hunt; It's For The Birds

description:
Overview

The escaped murderer and gene-splicing freak Dr. Polynice is out for revenge against Cal. And what's the best way to get that, since Cal himself has proven an elusive target? Strike at someone close to him. Will Cal's small inner circle shrink by one?

volume.name: Supernatural Freak Machine: A Cal McDonald Mystery

description:
Overview

An exclusive club forms at Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends, and Bloo makes the others do some pretty strange things to join.

  • Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends in The Elusive Exclusive
  • The Powerpuff Girls in Statue of Limitations
  • Camp Lazlo in Honky Dory
  • Dexter's Laboratory in Bill Nan The Science Man
name: The Elusive Exclusive; Statue of Limitations; Honky Dory; Bill Nan the Science Man

description:
Overview
Dr. Cindy Lyn, inventor of a new energy converter, is on the run. Pursued by a pair of hi-tech Cyber-Mercs, she finds herself trapped with an unlikely protector - a rice farmer with mystic-like powers who goes by the name Tsumi!

Glen Cadigan presents a haunting story of parental love gone very, very wrong in the present, while Brian Augustyn (Batman: Gotham By Gaslight) tells a tale of years gone by - and the British Empire's first contact with Cthulhu's agents of horror in the stunning "Empire Of Ants".
name: Empire Of Ants; The Awakening

description: A series of bizarre murders suggests that a long-dead villain has returned from the grave. The desperate New York police turn to the Man Without Fear, Daredevil, to solve the case. Daredevil, however, is unaware that Captain America is also investigatingâ¦
name: One-Shot

volume.name: Daredevil & Captain America: Dead On Arrival

description:
Overview
Lock your doors and windows the Surgeon is on the loose! The mystery surrounding the New Orleans serial killer deepens as Detectives O'Connor and Maddison discover some citizens of the Big Easy might not be what they appear. Will they find the evidence they need to save the next victim - or will they be too late again?

Overview
In the thrilling final issue of the mini-series, Asmodeus recalls his involvement with historyâs most infamous criminals and war mongers.Â  Then, under suspicion from Lucifer, Asmodeus finds himself in a predicamentÂ where he must deceive the Great Deceiver himself!!Â  This issue contains an exclusive interview with the creator and writer of the mini-series, Mitch Brown.Â  Also, character designs are included from artist Wilfredo Torres.
name: Book III of III

description: The original El Diablo rides again! Chato Santana, the new El Diablo, catches up with the man that crippled him while Lazarus Lane fights for his life against Vorpal. Only one El Diablo will live through this fight.
name: Chapter Three

description:
Overview
Ferryman Gideon Thorne won't let a little thing like being dead keep him from getting a job done, because when you're a Ferryman, failure is not an option. The question is: who's his target . . . and who is Thorne really working for?
name: Guess Who's Coming To Kill You?

description:
Overview
The intergalactic series comes to a supernova bang on the steps of Washington, DC! An epic battle between good and evil will determine the fate of not one, but two worlds! Prophecies are fulfilled, heroes are born, and the science of both worlds will be put to the test as the saucers continue their attack!

volume.name: Ray Harryhausen Presents: Flying Saucers Vs. The Earth

description:
Overview
Itâs Halloween night in a small Midwestern town, and five teenagers looking for a scare decide to take a trip to the most famous haunted house in the worldâThe Haunted Caves. But when they stumble upon the REAL Haunted Caves they must face their worst fears as they become the playthings of a maniacal killer hell-bent destroying their lives!
name: One-Shot

description: The demon Tuma'el stands poised to take control of London's very soul. Chas Chandler must save the city, and at the same time, rediscover his own place in his beloved London.
name: The Knowledge Conclusion

description:
They've had their differences lately, but with Batman infected by a virus and at death's door, Superman does no less than look for the cure at the heart of a comet in "Daughters of the Moon."

  1. Cover by Ed Hannigan and Klaus Janson.
  2. "Daughters of the Moon" written by L. B. Kellog and David Anthony Kraft, penciled by Jerome Moore, inked by Frank McLaughlin, colored by Carl Gafford and lettered by John Costanza.

Notes:

  • Lex Luthor and Joker cameo flashbacks.

"And Now... The Moon Dancers!"

"Superman III Movie Sweepstakes! Details Inside!"

Superman and Batman vs. Harvest Moon, Crescent Moon, and New Moon - the Moondancers trio.
name: Daughters of the Moon

description:
A humble young monk and a magical, shape-changing fox find themselves romantically drawn together, but as their love blooms, the fox learns of a devilish plot by a group of demons to steal the monk's life.

This is the tale of a humble young monk and a magical, shape-changing fox who find themselves romantically drawn together.

As their love blooms, the fox learns of a devilish plot by a group of demons to steal the monk's life. With the aid of Morpheus, the King of All Night's Dreamings, the fox must use all of her cunning and creative thinking to foil this evil scheme and save the man that she loves.

Divorce is tough for any teenager, but when your mother is a typical suburban soccer mom and your dad is a 300 foot tall, city trampling, battleship devouring monster things get even tougher. This is Duncan Rosenblatt's reality. His mom wants him to get into a good college, his dad wants him to go into the family business, namely conquering the earth and ascending to his rightful place as king of all monsters. Being the new kid at school isn't the easiest, especially when you're a 15-year-old, orange, half dragon. Duncan grapples with the fear and prejudice he encounters, all the while haunted by visions of the monster his father, the world-shaking monster known as Belloc, wants him to become. And just why is an elite United Nations strike force descending on Duncan's new hometown?
name: Growing Pains Chapter I

description: Divorce is tough for any teenager, but when your mother is a typical suburban soccer mom and your dad is a 300-foot-tall, city-trampling, battleship- devouring monster, things get even tougher! This is Duncan Rosenblatt's reality. His mom wants him to get into a good college; his dad wants him to go into the family business... namely conquering the Earth and ascending to his rightful place as king of all monsters!Â  So you think final exams are tough? Try being Duncan Rosenblatt. The tests his father puts him through will either make him a king or kill him. Like most children of divorce, Duncan spends every other weekend with his dad, but since his dad can stomp skyscrapers and his place is a hidden lair in an abandoned nuclear test site, it takes a super soldier like Col. Booshwa Barnes just to drop him off.
name: Growing Pains Chapter II

description: Divorce is tough for any teenager, but when your mother is a typical suburban soccer mom and your dad is a 300 foot tall, city trampling, battleship devouring monster things get even tougher. This is Duncan Rosenblatt's reality. His mom wants him to get into a good college, his dad wants him to go into the family business, namely conquering the earth and ascending to his rightful place as king of all monsters. Duncan's darkest nightmares become a reality when he is forced by his father to face another monster in savage combat. Are these brutal tests really meant to help him control his powers, as his father says, or to destroy his humanity? Back at home, the fragile relationships Duncan has forged with his fellow students are shattered by a shocking betrayal.
name: Growing Pains Chapter III

description: Divorce is tough for any teenager, but when your mother is a typical suburban soccer mom and your dad is a 300 foot tall, city trampling, battleship devouring monster things get even tougher. This is Duncan Rosenblatt's reality. His mom wants him to get into a good college, his dad wants him to go into the family business, namely conquering the Earth and ascending to his rightful place as king of all monsters. Duncan find himself trapped between two lives. Too humane to succeed in his father's world of conquest and battle, but too feral for the world of men, he abandons both and flees into the wilderness. His path is chosen for him when his mother is kidnapped and he must unleash his full fury to save her. Will the monster or the man triumph in the end?
name: Growing Pains Chapter IV

description: In 1963, Stan Lee and Jack Kirby launched a new title that featured a band of teenagers and their wheelchair-bound mentor, all possessing an "X-Tra" power that made them unique...and feared by humanity. UNCANNY X-MEN went through some early highs and lows before exploding back onto the scene in the late 1970s under the auspices of Chris Claremont, Dave Cockrum and John Byrne â fast becoming a phenomenon that would break out of the comics industry and become a worldwide sensation. It would make characters like Wolverine, Phoenix and Rogue household names, and launch the careers of talents like Paul Smith, Marc Silvestri, Jim Lee and Joe Madureira â to name just a few. In honor of UNCANNY X-MEN's milestone 500th issue, MARVEL SPOTLIGHT throws a party to celebrate one of the greatest comics of all time. Join us as we look back at 500 issues worth of amazing characters, top creative talent and some of the most powerful stories in the medium.
name: Uncanny X-Men 500 Issues Celebration

volume.name: Marvel Spotlight: Uncanny X-Men 500 Issues Celebration

description:
Introducing...Justice League Antarctica, with members Major Disaster, Big Sir, Clock King, Multi-Man and Cluemaster...all former members of the Injustice League. Who else could lead this gang of ex-villains but...G'nort?

Notes:

  • Annual numbering continues from Justice League International Annual #3.
  • Per the indica the title is Justice League Annual 4, while the cover states Justice League America.
  • The cover is a parody and a homage to Justice League #1.
  • On page 6 panel 2 the Dooley Diamond is named after the editor Kevin Dooley.
  • The Daily Planet headline article was written by "stuff writer" M. J. DeMatteis with photos by P. Porker.
name: What's Black and White and Black and White and Bl...

description: As the pieces of the story come back to Alfred, so do the pieces of the events that led up to his kidnapping.Â  Hush has found a new Clayface and intends to use it to attack Batman, but to what end?Â  What is the reason behind all this and why is Alfred so convinced he saw Tommy Elliot?Â  The end will surely shock you as Batman's line is cut once again!
name: The Shape of Things to Come, Part Two

description: Alfred has been under the influence of Hush since his kidnapping and as if that isn't enough he is not being framed for murder!Â  Batman races to both find a cure for infection that Alfred has, as well as try to clear his name, all while Hush is in the background slowly making moves that hinder the Batman.Â  The new version of Clayface is forced to work for Hush, now armed with a shape-shifter Hush proves to be all the more dangerous!
name: The Shape of Things to Come, Part Three

description: Batman is forced to do Hush's biding in order to save Alfred's life, including breaking a prisoner out of Arkham!Â  Batman free's a Clayface in hopes of curing his friend, but not all will go according to plan as Batman has to fight Clayface, Hush and the Police.Â  As if that isn't enough, if Clayface escapes, anything that happens next will fall on Batman!Â  Will Batman save the day and clear Alfred's name?Â
name: The Shape of Things to Come, Part Four

description: In a long-forgotten summer home that belonged to Thomas and Martha Wayne, a body turns up that will lead Bruce Wayne to a part of his parents' past he never imagined existed, forcing him to ask himself if his parents' marriage was nothing but a sham, the outcome could tear down everything Bruce Wayne thought he knew about his family!
name: The Letter

description:
"Nothing personal... It's just revenge."

In the bleak world of the swordsman, it is said that he who becomes the No. 1 samurai shall rule the world. And only No. 2 is allowed to challenge No. 1. Afro Samurai has assumed the mantle of No. 2, seeking vengeance against No. 1, a gunman who killed his father years ago. But assassins lurk at every corner, seeking to rob Afro Samurai of the title of No. 2. Can Afro survive long enough to exact his revenge?
name: Volume 1

description: From the conclusion of the first season to the opening of a new season of stories, Frank Cho and Murray are taking the action underground, and underwater as more clues regarding Jana, the undisputed Queen of the Jungle, finds out more about her mysterious past, and the mysterious island she call home!
name: Jungle Girl Season 2

description: Thought lost in a plane crash, the girl that would be known as Sheena, the powerful and beautiful Queen of the Jungle defied logic, and not only survivied, but thrived in the wilds of South America. Now an adult, she is discovered and brought back to civilization... where the war for supremacy truly begins! Sheena is back, and ready for the 21st century!
name: 99-cent Special

description: An academic studying the jungle is murdered, and all signs point toward the impossible - the legend of the Mapinguari is real! Does the "boogeyman" of the jungle exist? An expedition deep into the uncharted jungle for answers to the murder causes Sheena to get involved. Can the quest be completed before all who are on it die horrible deaths?
name: Trail of the Mapinguari

description: The steamy jungle adventure continues! What is it about the snarling, ferocious, wild girl that's being held captive in Val Verde's hospital that attracts the attention of a huge corporation like Cardwell Industries? Why is Cardwell's CEO so threatened by this girl? Why is she so blessedly sexy? All this plus Sheena vs... a doorknob?!
name: Sheena Queen of the Jungle

description: In the big city and on the run from the corrupt Cardwell Industries, Sheena finds herself needing a disguise... And in this case, hiding in plain sight is her only choice! She's survived everything that the brutal jungle has thrown at her in her life... can she survive cocktail dresses, high heels and clutch purses?!
name: Sheena Queen of the Jungle

description: "See Sonic! Sea Battle! See Sonic Sea Battle!": By order of the President, Sonic and his friends embark on a special search and recover mission to retrieve a powerful energy source...and it just may be a Chaos Emerald! The only problem is, it is at the bottom of the ocean, and we all know water is Sonic's greatest weakness. Speaking of weaknesses, Eggman has a weakness for power, so you know he's out to get that Chaos Emerald, too!
name: See Sonic! Sea Battle!

description: With forces pursing her from every side, Sheena makes a run for the only place she knows she'll be safe - and once she makes it into the embrace of the jungle, her pursuers will come to know firsthand what the call of the wild really sounds like! All-out steamy jungle action issue! Don't miss the unbelievable twist on the last page of this issue!
name: Sheena Queen of the Jungle

description: "Field Trip of Doom": When a mysterious Doctor invites Chris, Sonic and their friends on a field trip to the space museum, evil goes into orbit! Sonic and crew are left in a dire situation as Eggman's sinister plan unfolds. What could it be?
name: Field Trip of Doom!

description: The title says it all: Eggman has been secretly, methodically building the biggest, baddest bots ever! Even the combined might of Sonic, Rogue, Knuckles, Tails and more may falter in the face of this fearsome development. Worst of all, if Sonic succeeds, it could be at the cost of his friends! Jaw-dropping moments in this shocking conclusion!
name: Boisterous Bot Battle!

description: The creepy basement in the House of Mystery doesn't hold your average trinkets and cast-aside items. In fact, among the bits catalogued you'll find the diary of "Cain," one stained and bloody bed sheet, chains of assorted lengths, something slick and wet grinding over the stones, a maze and a minotaur. It's chapter 2 of "Love Stories for Dead People" and you'll never look at basements the same way again!
name: Beneath the Skin: Chapter Two of Love Stories for Dead People

description: Who is Sheena? Is she really who everyone thinks she is, or are those claims full of hot water? One thing's for sure: Val Verde will never be the same once the truth comes out - and it happens here!
name: Sheena Queen of the Jungle

description: The fate of the earth hangs in the balance as the reason behind Eggman's kidnapping of the sweet, peaceful Chao named Cheese is further revealed! Sonic, Tails and their friends face their biggest challenge yet as they struggle to save the planet from mass destruction!
name: I Never Promised You A Chao Garden - Part 1

description: Eggman's evil scheme has the usually peaceful Chao going crazy, and chaos reigns! Will Sonic, Tails and Knuckles be swift enough to slow the onslaught? More importantly, is Uncle Chuck smart enough to figure out how to return the Chao to normal? Your one-stop-shop for answers is this senses-shattering issue!
name: I Never Promised You A Chao Garden - Part 2

description: "Take this Job and Shovel It": When city sewer workers unwittingly unleash ProtoShadow, Topaz and Rogue are assigned to investigate. This upsets Cowboy, who feels he was unfairly overlooked for the assignment. Cowboy orchestrates an investigation of his own, and deceives Sonic into coming along. Before too long, they're setting off defense systems and ducking enemy drones! Meanwhile, ProtoShadow tails Topaz and Rogue, hoping they can clue him in to his own identity. It's more mystery, action and intrigue based on the hit cartoon series! >
name: Take This Job and Shovel It!

description: "Wicked Sweet Shuttle Shenanigans": A rousing adventure that takes Sonic and friends off to far away lands! The World's Fair in Paris hosts the unveiling of the New Thorndyke Industries space shuttle, and you don't think a little detail like that would escape the eye of Eggman, do you? Agent Topaz and Rouge are on the case, but when it's revealed that Emerl has been following them, will this mean disaster? Look out for Big the Cat and Froggy to finally make a big noise in the Sonic X comic as everything goes wild at the World's Fair!
name: Wicked Sweet Shuttle Shenanigans - Part 1

description: WICKED SWEET SHUTTLE SHENANIGANS: Part 2: Turning things up a few notches from the previous issue, Eggman ups the ante in his quest to pilfer the Thorndyke space shuttle by unleashing a gigantic spider robot at the World's Fair! Emerl continues to lurk in the background, begging the question, is Emerl friend of foe? An all-out battle ensues as Sonic, Knuckles, Tails, Rogue, Big the Cat and more give it their all to save the city! It's action and intrigue in the hit "Sonic X" animated series style! Frantic thrills 'n chills cover by Spaz!
name: Wicked Sweet Shuttle Shenanigans - Part 2

description: In these days of ultra-serious megacrossovers, comics gets exactly what it's been needingâa jolt of adrenaline courtesy of the too-long-absent Tank Girl! Co-creator Alan C. Martin is back to offer redemption to anyone who sat through the Tank Girl movie, and what's more, this time the book's art chores will be handled by artist/painter and fellow Aussie, Ashley Wood! Issue 1 features six separate Tank Girl stories by Martin and Wood, including appearances by Jet Girl, the Funsters and more.

The landmark series originally published by Marvel UK makes its IDW debut! In the first issue of this special re-presentation of the story spinning out of the TRANSFORMERS Animated Movie, writer Simon Furman and artist Geoff Senior begin a stars-spanning tale where GALVATRON travels back in time to construct a weapon with which to destroy UNICRON once and for all, and takes on the depleted AUTOBOTS at the same time! All that and a brand-new cover recreation by artist Nick Roche, too!

The landmark Marvel UK series continues as GALVATRON continues to scheme with the aid of the CONSTRUCTICONS as ULTRA MAGNUS arrives on Earth to search for OPTIMUS Prime. But unfortunately JAZZ is captured and at the mercy of GALVATRON. Will the AUTOBOTS be able to save him in time? Writer Simon Furman and artists Jeff Anderson and Will Simpson continue this epic tale. Nick Roche once again provides an all-new cover!

The special reprint of this beloved U.K. TRANSFORMERS tale continues here with two new Chapters in one comic! On CYBERTON, the WRECKERS continue to train for Operation Volcano. STARSCREAM is shocked with the discovery of MEGATRON's new and unlikely alliance with the AUTOBOTS. And GALVATRON reveals a secret to JAZZ. Writer Simon Furman and artists Jeff Anderson and Will Simpson continue this epic tale. Nick Roche once again provides an all-new cover re-creating a classic scene from the issue!

The special reprint of this beloved U.K. TRANSFORMERS tale continues here with two new chapters in one comic! The epic tale of Target: 2006 comes to a conclusion as the future AUTOBOTS put their plan into action and GALVATRON returnsâand he's angry. From writer Simon Furman and artists Geoff Senior, Jeff Anderson and Will Simpson. Nick Roche once again provides an all-new cover re-creating a classic scene from the issue!

Ever wondered what form your favorite Transformers would take if they existed in different eras? Wonder no more, as IDWâs new Evolutions line will look at some special out-of-continuity tales involving the Robots in Disguise. The line makes its debut in June with the four-part Hearts of Steel. In this standalone miniseries, writer Chuck Dixon and Transformers artist supreme Guido Guidi transplant the âbots to the Industrial Revolution, where a charismatic hammer-man named John Henry discovers that a steam drill is really an alien robot named Bumblebee. Before he can process this information, the pair are attacked by Decepticons disguised as tanks, trains and walking engines. Is this all part of a larger scheme by Starscream? And if so, will the other Autobots arrive in time to stop his nefarious plans?
name: Hearts of Steel, Part 1

description: Chuck Dixon and artist Guido Guidi continue their special look at the Industrial Age reign of the Transformers. In The Transformers Evolutions: Hearts of Steel, part 2, Starscream plans to usher in an all-new age, one that means doom for John Henry and his iron-age Autobot associates.
name: Hearts of Steel, Part 2

description: "No Thanks for the Memories": Part 2 (of 2) Sonic's 15th Anniversary adventure continues in Sonic X! Sonic, Amy Rose, Knuckles and Tails are trapped in a Virtual Reality universe powered by the Master Emerald. Now our Heroes must battle their way back to their friends who believe they have been left behind forever! Will Sonic be abandoned by his mistaken friends? Will Eggman win and destroy his hated nemesis? Will Bukkun's mad desire for sugary treats be the undoing of everything!
name: No Thanks For The Memories! - Part 2
